02:12.382 --> 02:14.123
I'M SURE OF THAT, NEDRA.

02:14.176 --> 02:18.795
WELL, GOOD-BYE
FOR NOW, THEN.

02:18.889 --> 02:21.051
GOOD-BYE, ANNE, DEAR.

02:21.141 --> 02:25.135
OH, YOU POOR,
POOR LITTLE DEARS.

02:25.187 --> 02:29.272
<i>POOR, UNHAPPY
LITTLE DEARS.</i>

02:29.358 --> 02:31.395
GOOD-BYE, CHILDREN.

02:31.485 --> 02:34.352
<i>(children)
BYE, AUNT NEDRA.</i>

02:34.446 --> 02:36.232
SHE WANTS TO
TAKE US AWAY,

02:36.323 --> 02:37.404
DOESN'T SHE, DAD?

02:37.491 --> 02:38.981
DOES SHE, DADDY?

02:39.076 --> 02:43.912
<i>IS THAT WHAT
SHE WAS HERE FOR?</i>

02:43.997 --> 02:45.374
SHE DOESN'T APPROVE

02:45.457 --> 02:47.323
OF THE WAY I'M
BRINGING YOU UP.

02:47.376 --> 02:48.912
SHE SAYS
I'M TOO BUSY.

02:49.002 --> 02:50.788
PERHAPS I AM.

02:50.879 --> 02:54.622
SHE SAYS THAT YOUR SITTERS
AND NURSES HAVE BEEN, UH,

02:54.716 --> 02:57.834
WELL, TOO MEAN
OR TOO NICE...

02:57.886 --> 03:04.258
