11:02.537 --> 11:05.325
A KEY.

11:05.373 --> 11:06.659
<i>YOU DON'T WIND
ROBOTS UP.</i>

11:06.708 --> 11:08.039
THEY RUN
ON ELECTRICITY.

11:16.843 --> 11:22.509
BUT YOU DO WANT PROOF
THOUGH, DON'T YOU?

11:22.557 --> 11:28.098
<i>(Tom, off) AND IF SHE
HAD EYES LIKE THESE...</i>

11:28.188 --> 11:30.725
<i>(Karen, off) OH, IF SHE
ONL Y HAD LONG HAIR.</i>

11:34.485 --> 11:37.068
I SEE YOU
HAVE A KITE.

11:37.155 --> 11:38.395
GET IT.

11:38.489 --> 11:41.106
BUT I'M ALL
OUT OF STRING.

11:41.201 --> 11:43.363
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

11:43.453 --> 11:44.614
THERE.

11:52.337 --> 11:55.079
IT'S FLYING!

11:55.173 --> 11:57.756
WHAT DID YOU SAY
MY NAME WAS?

11:57.842 --> 11:58.923
GRANDMA!

12:01.554 --> 12:04.922
HEY, ANNE, LOOK VVHAT
GRANDMA'S DONE! LOOK!

12:05.016 --> 12:06.882
HOW HIGH SHALL
WE FLY IT?

12:06.976 --> 12:08.137
THE MOON.

12:08.228 --> 12:10.014
THE MOON IT IS.

12:14.776 --> 12:16.733
OH, GRANDMA!

13:25.847 --> 13:27.554
DAD! DAD!

13:27.640 --> 13:30.382
GRANDMA, IS THAT
A NEW CAR OUT FRONT?

13:30.476 --> 13:31.978
ASK YOUR FATHER.

13:32.061 --> 13:33.802
DAD, IS THAT
OUR CAR?!

13:33.855 --> 13:35.892
IT SURE IS. I CAME HOME
EARLY TO SURPRISE YOU.

13:35.982 --> 13:37.564
CAN WE TAKE A
RIDE IN IT?

13:37.650 --> 13:38.685
WELL, OF COURSE
WE CAN.

13:38.776 --> 13:40.312
WHERE'S ANNE?

13:40.361 --> 13:42.193
SHE WANTED TO STAY
IN THIS AFTERNOON.

13:42.280 --> 13:44.237
YOU CHILDREN GO ON OUT AND
PLAY FOR A LITTLE VVHILE.

13:44.324 --> 13:45.940
I'LL BE OUT
IN A FEW MINUTES.

13:46.034 --> 13:47.820
<i>THEN WE'LL RUN DOWN
TO THE SODA FOUNTPAN,</i>

13:47.910 --> 13:49.571
HOW ABOUT THAT?

13:49.662 --> 13:50.743
<i>(Karen) WONDERFUL! COME ON, TOM.</i>

13:56.961 --> 14:00.044
I'M SORRY ABOUT ANNE.

14:00.131 --> 14:01.667
YOU'VE BEEN GOOD TO US,

14:01.758 --> 14:03.248
AND FOR US.

14:03.343 --> 14:08.759
NOW, DON'T WORRY
ABOUT ANNE.

14:08.848 --> 14:12.591
SHE'LL ACCEPT ME...
EVENTUALLY.

14:12.685 --> 14:14.551
YOU SEE, MR. ROGERS,

14:14.645 --> 14:18.354
CHILDREN ARE THE MOST COMPLICATED
THINGS IN THE VVORLD.

14:18.441 --> 14:20.523
I COULD BE THE GREATEST
COOK IN THE WORLD,

14:20.568 --> 14:23.401
THE FINEST,
MOST EXCITING PLAYMATE,

14:23.488 --> 14:26.025
THE MOST INCREDIBLY
INTERESTING COMPANION,

14:26.074 --> 14:29.362
BUT THOSE
ARE VERY TINY NICHES--

14:29.410 --> 14:34.029
A SHELF IN THE STOMACH, A VERY
SMALL LEDGE IN THE BRAIN.

14:34.123 --> 14:36.410
IT'S THE HEART
I HAVE TO ENTER--

14:36.501 --> 14:38.242
THE CHILD'S HEART--

14:38.336 --> 14:42.375
AND THIS IS A DEEP PLACE,
DIFFICULT TO REACH.

14:42.423 --> 14:44.414
<i>BUT THAT TOO
WILL COME.</i>

14:51.599 --> 14:53.135
ANNE, WE'RE
GOING FOR A RIDE.

14:53.226 --> 14:54.432
WILL YOU COME
WITH US?

14:54.519 --> 14:56.430
I WANT TO STAY HOME.

14:56.521 --> 14:58.603
I DON'T WANT
HER HERE.

14:58.689 --> 15:00.100
ANNE, YOU
MUSTN'T SAY THAT.

15:00.191 --> 15:01.898
I DON'T WANT
HER HERE!

15:01.943 --> 15:03.650
(Grandma) DO I BOTHER YOU, ANNE?

15:03.736 --> 15:05.477
I NEVER WANTED
YOU HERE.

15:05.571 --> 15:09.109
IT WAS THEM-- FATHER
AND TOM AND KAREN.

15:09.200 --> 15:12.158
THEY WANTED YOU,
BUT I DIDN'T.

15:12.245 --> 15:15.579
THEY NEEDED YOU, BUT
I NEVER NEEDED YOU.

15:15.665 --> 15:16.655
<i>(father)
ANNE.</i>

15:16.749 --> 15:18.615
BUT IT'S TRUE.

15:18.709 --> 15:20.575
YOU SIT AND
YOU TALK TO HER,

15:20.670 --> 15:22.911
<i>AND YOU EAT THE
FOOD SHE MAKE-S',</i>

15:22.964 --> 15:25.501
<i>AND YOU MAKE
BELIEVE, FATHER.</i>

15:25.591 --> 15:27.093
<i>THAT'S WHAT YOU DO.</i>

15:27.135 --> 15:28.921
<i>YOU MAKE BELIEVE</i>

15:28.970 --> 15:31.302
<i>AS IF IT
WERE A GAME.</i>

15:31.389 --> 15:33.471
AS IF SHE WERE REAL.

15:33.558 --> 15:35.265
BUT SHE'S NOT REAL.

15:35.309 --> 15:36.765
SHE'S A MACHINE.

15:36.853 --> 15:38.844
